    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm looking into some new high-protein food options for my 9 year old labrador. He's starting to slow down a bit. What's a good target protein to fat ratio for an aging lab to maintain muscle without adding too much weight?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A target protein to fat ratio for an aging Labrador is a tricky one, but you'll want to aim for something that keeps the muscle solid without making him feel sluggish. Look for formulas that lean towards a higher protein content, maybe in the range of 25% to 30% protein, depending on his activity level. If you go too low on the protein, he'll start to lose that good, sturdy muscle, and you don't want him becoming a floppy, slow-moving sack of bones. Remember, a good, dense muscle is what you want, not just fluff!",
